cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a robot navigating through dense scenarios and crowds. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses a Deep Reinforcement Learning-based (DRL) collision avoidance method. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the method involves sensing and predicting the trajectories of pedestrians. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the method involves computing a deviation velocity to avoid potential freezing zones and account for social constraints. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses a hybrid approach combining the Frozone algorithm with a DRL-based collision avoidance method.
